│ ### 2. Analysis of the Reproducer IR                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The IR contains four consecutive stores to an array allocated on the stack (`%h`), followed by a volatile store that aliases │
│ with the first of these stores.                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```llvm                                                                                                                      │
│ ; ...                                                                                                                        │
│ store i32 %add4, ptr %h, align 16           ; Store 0                                                                        │
│ ; ...                                                                                                                        │
│ store i32 %add6, ptr %arrayinit.element, align 4 ; Store 1                                                                   │
│ ; ...                                                                                                                        │
│ store i32 %add6, ptr %arrayinit.element7, align 8 ; Store 2                                                                  │
│ ; ...                                                                                                                        │
│ %call12 = tail call i32 @fn1(i32 %add)                                                                                       │
│ store i32 %call12, ptr %arrayinit.element10, align 4 ; Store 3                                                               │
│ ; ...                                                                                                                        │
│ store volatile i32 0, ptr %h, align 4      ; Volatile store, aliases with Store 0                                            │
│ ret void                                                                                                                     │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The SLP vectorizer identifies these four stores as a potential candidate for vectorization. However, there are complex       │
│ dependencies:                                                                                                                │
│ 1.  The value for Store 3 comes from a function call (`%call12`), which has side effects.                                    │
│ 2.  The volatile store at the end writes to the same location as Store 0. This means Store 0 must execute before the         │
│ volatile store.                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The SLP vectorizer's scheduler builds a dependency graph to determine if the instructions can be reordered for               │
